<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN215-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, pāṭāṇṭiṇai. tuṟai, iyaṉmoḻi. kōpperuñcōḻaṉ picirāntaiyār vārāreṉṟa cāṉṟōrk kavar varuvāreṉṟu colliyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN215">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kavaikkatir varaki ṉavaippuṟu vākka</l>
<l>ṟāteru maṟukiṟ pōtoṭu potuḷiya</l>
<l>vēḷai veṇpū veṇṭayir koḷīi</l>
<l>yāymaka ḷaṭṭa vampuḷi mitavai</l>
<l>yavarai koyyuna rāra māntun</l>
<l>teṉṉam poruppa ṉaṉṉāṭ ṭuḷḷum</l>
<l>picirō ṉeṉpave ṉuyirōm punaṉē</l>
<l>celvak kālai niṟpiṉu</l>
<l>mallaṟ kālai nillalaṉ maṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="6">Even in the good land of the one from the Southern heights, </l>
<l corresp="5">where those who pluck field beans feed to satiation </l>
<l corresp="4">on the sweet-sour food that was cooked by a cowherd woman </l>
<l corresp="1">from a pounded preparation of fork-eared wild millet, </l>
<l corresp="3">imbuing white curd with the white flower of Vēḷai, </l>
<l corresp="2">that was full with buds from the street with pollen [and] dung, </l>
<l corresp="7">the one they call Picirōṉ will protect my life. </l>
<l corresp="8">Even though he may stay [away] at a time of affluence, </l>
<l corresp="9">he will not stay [away] at a time of affliction. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
